ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES

The Lynx Chemical Group-Dalton plant has a long-standing commitment to worker and public safety and to the protection of the environment.  We are committed to operating and maintaining all of our processes in a safe and responsible manner, as demonstrated by the resources we invest to prevent accidents.  As a member of the Synthetic Organic Chemical Manufacturer?s Association, we adhere to the principles of Responsible Care.  As such, we are in the process of developing an Environmental Management System to continue improvement in Environmental, Health and Safety programs.  In addition to ensuring that our employees have the best training in the operation of our processes, we demand that safety be the first priority in the design, installation, operation and maintenance of our processes.

It is the policy of Lynx Chemical Group to develop, manufacture, and distribute materials with minimal impact on the environment and without injury to our employees, customers, and community.  To that end, Lynx Chemical Group is committed to:

?    The protection of the health, safety, and security of our employees and facilities;
?    Complying with all applicable federal, state and local Environmental, Health, Safety, and Security regulations and our other related voluntary requirements including Responsible Care;
?    Continual reduction of the impact of our operations on the environment through ongoing pollution prevention programs;
?    Continual communications and openness with our stakeholders;
?    Training all employees regarding the importance of EHS&S protection and roles they play as stewards.vironmental, Health and Safety programs.  

